text: Isaac Palazón Camacho (born 6 January 1994), commonly known as Isi, is a Spanish footballer who plays for Rayo Vallecano as a left winger. ==Club career== Isi was born in Cieza, Murcia, and made his senior debut with CD Cieza at the age of just 15, after spending a short period at Real Madrid's La Fábrica. He subsequently moved to Villarreal CF's youth setup, reaching the C-team before being released in 2013; he then returned to his first club Cieza. In 2014, Isi joined Real Murcia and was initially assigned to the reserves in Tercera División. On 18 December of that year, he agreed to a new three-year contract with the club, being definitely promoted to the main squad in Segunda División B the following year. On 18 August 2017, Isi moved to fellow third division side SD Ponferradina, after terminating his contract with Murcia. He contributed with eight goals in 40 appearances during the 2018–19 season, as his side returned to Segunda División after a three-year absence. Isi made his professional debut on 18 August 2019, starting in a 1–3 away loss against Cádiz CF. He scored his first goal in the category on 26 October, netting his team's second in a 3–1 away defeat of Rayo Vallecano On 23 January 2020, Isi signed a three-and-a-half-year contract with fellow second division side Rayo. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:People from Cieza, Murcia Category:Spanish footballers Category:Murcian footballers Category:Association football wingers Category:Segunda División players Category:Segunda División B players Category:Tercera División players Category:Villarreal CF C players Category:Real Murcia Imperial players Category:Real Murcia players Category:SD Ponferradina players Category:Rayo Vallecano players
